view-if: communist_candidate >= 50

tbd

@sapd_wins
view-if: sapd_candidate >= 50

tbd

@spd_wins
view-if: spd_candidate >= 50

tbd

@independent_wins
view-if: unaffiliate_candidate >= 50

tbd

@bourgeois_wins
view-if: bourgeois_candidate >= 50

tbd

@nsdap_wins
view-if: nsdap_candidate >= 50

tbd

@spd_campaign_hq
view-if: spd_turn and spd_candidate

We are attempting to be elected to the office of chairmanship. To this end, we will have to forge alliances with other factions vying for the same.

- @court_kpd: Court the KPD.
- @court_sapd: Court the SAPD.
- @court_unaffiliated: Court the unaffiliated.
- @court_bourgeois: Court the bourgeois.
- @cou


@spd_majority
view-if: effective_spd_s >= 50
on-arrival: spd_soviets = 1; executive_formed = 1

With a majority of the delegates, we have the capacity to elect a Social Democratic chairman. There still remains the matter of which faction the chairman should come from, however.

- @left
- @center
- @reformist
- @labor
- @neorevisionist

@left
title: The Left.
subtitle: [+ spd_left_s +]%
view-if: (((left_strength+center_strength >= reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+labor_strength) and (left_strength >= center_strength) and (center_dissent < center_strength)) or ((left_strength+labor_strength >= reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+center_strength) and (left_strength >= labor_strength) and (labor_dissent < labor_strength))) and ((spd_s - spd_reformist_s - spd_neorevisionist_s) >= 50)
on-arrival: left_soviets = 1; left_strength += 5; pro_republic -= 2; socialism += 2; z_relation -= 3; dvp_relation -= 5; ddp_relation -= 5; kpd_relation += 3
go-to: optional_coalitions

Toni Sender is elected to chair the councils, representing a firm though not too firm leftist line in the leadership of the new institution. 

@center
title: The Center
subtitle: [+ spd_center_s +]%
view-if: (not (((((reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+center_strength >= left_strength+labor_strength) and (reformist_strength >= center_strength) and (center_dissent < center_strength)) or ((reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+labor_strength >= left_strength+center_strength) and (reformist_strength >= labor_strength) and (labor_dissent < labor_strength))) and spd_neorevisionist_s < 50) and ((spd_s - spd_left_s) >= 50)) and not ((((left_strength+center_strength >= reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+labor_strength) and (left_strength >= center_strength) and (center_dissent < center_strength)) or ((left_strength+labor_strength >= reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+center_strength) and (left_strength >= labor_strength) and (labor_dissent < labor_strength))) and ((spd_s - spd_reformist_s - spd_neorevisionist_s) >= 50)) and not (spd_neorevisionist_s >= 50)) and spd_center_s >= spd_labor_s
on-arrival: center_soviets = 1; center_strength += 5
go-to: optional_coalitions

Rudolf Breitscheid is elected to chair the councils, representing a middle road between the revolutionaries and the reformists.

@reformist
title: The Reformists
subtitle: [+ spd_reformist_s +]%
view-if: ((((reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+center_strength >= left_strength+labor_strength) and (reformist_strength >= center_strength) and (center_dissent < center_strength)) or ((reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+labor_strength >= left_strength+center_strength) and (reformist_strength >= labor_strength) and (labor_dissent < labor_strength))) and spd_neorevisionist_s < 50) and ((spd_s - spd_left_s) >= 50)
on-arrival: reformist_soviets = 1; reformist_strength += 5; socialism -= 2; pro_republic += 2; z_relation += 2; ddp_relation += 2; kpd_relation -= 4; left_dissent += 3
go-to: optional_coalitions

Marie Juchacz is elected to chair the councils, representing a strong reformist tendency that remains within the workers, and a seeming unreadiness by them to assume state power.

@labor
title: The Trade unions
subtitle: [+ spd_labor_s +]%
view-if: (not (((((reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+center_strength >= left_strength+labor_strength) and (reformist_strength >= center_strength) and (center_dissent < center_strength)) or ((reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+labor_strength >= left_strength+center_strength) and (reformist_strength >= labor_strength) and (labor_dissent < labor_strength))) and spd_neorevisionist_s < 50) and ((spd_s - spd_left_s) >= 50)) and not ((((left_strength+center_strength >= reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+labor_strength) and (left_strength >= center_strength) and (center_dissent < center_strength)) or ((left_strength+labor_strength >= reformist_strength+neorevisionist_strength+center_strength) and (left_strength >= labor_strength) and (labor_dissent < labor_strength))) and ((spd_s - spd_reformist_s - spd_neorevisionist_s) >= 50)) and not (spd_neorevisionist_s >= 50)) and spd_labor_s >= spd_center_s
on-arrival: labor_soviets = 1; labor_strength += 5
go-to: optional_coalitions

Rudolf Wissell is elected to chair the councils, representing the interests of the trade unions and organized labor in this emerging form of labor organization.

@neorevisionist
title: The Neorevisionists
subtitle: [+ spd_neorevisionist_s +]%
view-if: spd_neorevisionist_s >= 50
on-arrival: neorevisionist_soviets = 1
go-to: optional_coalitions

Surprisingly, the Neorevisionists have taken a lead, electing Carlo Mierendorff to chair the councils. 

@optional_coalitions
go-to: oc_menu

With an SPD chair elected, however, remains the issue of the wider council executive. With us possessing a majority, we could choose to distribute positions simply within the SPD; but this would risk giving the councils the appearance of a mere party organ and undermining their budding legitimacy, especially when they currently possess no inherent power beyond that granted by the voluntary participation of workers within them.

@oc_menu

- @spd_only: Distribute positions exclusively within the party.
- @invite_sapd: Invite the SAPD.
- @invite_kpd: Invite the KPD.
- @invite_unaffiliate: Invite the unaffiliated.
- @invite_bourgeois: Invite the bourgeois-aligned.
- @done: We are done. 

@spd_only
view-if: not buttons_mashed
on-arrival: socialism -= (10-(spd_s/10)); left_dissent -= 5; center_dissent -= 5; labor_dissent -= 5; reformist_dissent -= 5; neorevisionist_dissent -= 5
subtitle: This may at least reduce dissent within the party.
go-to: done

The legitimacy and capacity of the councils is hurt by our unwillingness to distribute positions amongst other forces within the councils. In the end, the executive is made into an effective party organ, and those forces opposed to our party simply urge their councils to noncooperation with this executive.

@invite_sapd
view-if: not sapd_included and sapd_formed and sapd_s
subtitle: Former Social Democrats, they are willing.
choose-if: not bourgeois_included
unavailable-subtitle: With the bourgeois? Yeah, right.
on-arrival: buttons_mashed += 1; sapd_included = 1; socialism += 1; left_strength += 3; left_dissent -= 6; kpd_relation += 2; z_relation -= 2; ddp_relation -= 4; dvp_relation -= 5
go-to: oc_menu

We have invited the SAPD to our executive, and they have agreed. This has given the council a more left-wing orientation, as the SAPD stands firmly opposed to the disempowerment of the councils.

@invite_kpd
view-if: not kpd_included and not reformist_soviets and not neorevisionist_soviets
subtitle: The Communists are willing.
choose-if: (left_soviets or kpd_relation >= 50) and not bourgeois_included
unavailable-subtitle: The Communists are unwilling to enter the executive as it stands, opposing our chairmanship wholly.
on-arrival: kpd_included = 1; reichstag_enemy = 1; socialism += 2; kpd_relation += 5; left_strength += 5; left_dissent -= 5; z_relation -= 5; ddp_relation -= 6; dvp_relation -= 8
go-to: oc_menu

We have invited the KPD to our executive, and they have agreed to join. This has given the council a vastly more left-wing orientation, opening itself up to a chorral of criticism from the bourgeois parties who have begun to view the councils with concern as parallel power structures genuinely invested in the overthrow of the existing ones.

@invite_unaffiliate
view-if: not unaffiliate_included and unaffiliate_s
subtitle: Independent workers' representatives with largely economic and sectorial concerns.
on-arrival: buttons_mashed += 1; unaffiliate_included = 1; workers_spd += 3*(1-dissent); workers_other -= 3*(1-dissent)
go-to: oc_menu

By including the unaffiliated representatives in the executive, we are politicizing them positively. 

@invite_bourgeois
view-if: not bourgeois_included and not left_soviets
subtitle: The bourgeois-aligned representatives who demand the dissolution of the councils.
choose-if: (reformist_soviets or neorevisionist_soviets or (reformist_strength > left_strength and dvp_relation >= 40)) and not kpd_included and not sapd_included
unavailable-subtitle: The bourgeois representatives squarely refuse.
on-arrival: bourgeois_included; socialism -= 3; left_dissent += 10; left_strength -= 5; socialism -= 4; pro_republic += 4; kpd_relation -= 7; capital_strike_progress -= 1 if capital_strike_progress >= 6
go-to: oc_menu

The bourgeois representatives are invited to the executive and promptly join. The KPD assaults and derides us as betraying the revolutionary opportunity once more, while the bourgeoisie take relief in the fact that the councils are being tamed.

@done
view-if: buttons_mashed

With the executive assembled, the congress of councils is dismissed for the time being, to begin its affairs accordingly.



@kpd_majority
tags: other_forces
title: A Communist Chairman
view-if: kpd_s >= 50
subtitle: [+ kpd_s +]% - The Communists have won
on-arrival: reichstag_enemy = 1; kpd_soviets = 1; communist_influence += 3 if communist_influence; rfb_militancy += 0.1; rfb_militancy += (socialism/10); rb_strength -= left_strength; rfb_strength += left_strength; workers_kpd += (socialism/10); executive_formed = 1

The KPD has won chairmanship and control over the workers' councils coordinating bodies, and have immediately attempted to direct them towards the revolutionary path of seeking absolute control over the state, turning their attention squarely to the Reichstag as principal enemy.

@revolutionary
title: A Revolutionary Chairman
view-if: revolutionary_s >= 50
subtitle: [+ revolutionary_s +]% - The Revolutionaries have won
on-arrival: reichstag_enemy = 1; revolutionary_soviets = 1; rfb_militancy += 0.05; rfb_militancy += (socialism/10); rb_strength -= left_strength; rfb_strength += left_strength; workers_kpd += (socialism/20); executive_formed = 1
tags: other_forces

The Revolutionaries have together won chairmanship, with some disagreement within their tent, they have nonetheless put these aside to unify the councils against the Reichstag for the goal of full worker control, of transferring all political power to the soviets.

@left
title: A Leftist Chairman
view-if: left_coalition_s >= 50
subtitle: [+ left_coalition_s +]% - The Leftists have won
on-arrival: leftist_soviets = 1; rfb_militancy += (socialism/20); left_strength += 5; kpd_relation += 5; socialism += 1; reichstag_enemy = 1; executive_formed = 1
tags: other_forces

The Leftists have together won chairmanship, championing eventual empowerment of the councils over the Reichstag, even though the Communists would like to proactively launch a revolution, and even as those to the left of the Communists continue adventuristically preparing so.

@spd_majority
title: A Social-Democratic Chairman
view-if: (spd_s+unaffiliate_s) >= 50
subtitle: [+ spd_s +]% - The SPD has won!
on-arrival: spd_soviets = 1; executive_formed = 1
frequency: 100

The SPD has won leadership of the councils! The maintenance of this majority will rest upon ensuring the unity of the party's factions.

@united_front
title: A Socialist Chairman
view-if: (united_front_s+unaffiliate_s) >= 50 and kpd_relation >= 60
subtitle: [+ united_front_s +]% - The United Front has won
on-arrival: united_soviets = 1; rfb_militancy += (socialism/25); left_strength += 5; kpd_relation += 10; socialism += 2; reichstag_enemy = 1; executive_formed = 1
frequency: 50

The United Front has won the chairmanship, dividing executive positions between the SPD and the KPD and securing the support of the councils for the broader socialist agenda shared by the two parties.

@dissolutionist
title: A Parliamentarian Chairman
view-if: (dissolutionist_s+unaffiliate_s) >= 50
subtitle: [+ dissolutionist_s +]% - The Parliamentarians have won
on-arrival: parliamentarian_soviets = 1; socialism -= 2; pro_republic += 3; left_strength -= 5; kpd_relation -= 5; executive_formed = 1
frequency: 100

The councils have elected an executive actively in favor of the disempowerment of the councils in favor of the Reichstag, proving the unreadiness of the German working class for socialism in what some are calling a political suicide club.


